 Air Peace airline has deployed its aircraft to evacuate Nigerians who are stranded in Europe following the invasion of Ukraine by Russia. The airline’s spokesman, Stanley Olisa, said this in a statement in Lagos, on Thursday. “This is the first batch of Nigerians to be evacuated since the war broke out. “The aircraft departed Nigeria at 2:20am today, March 3, for Warsaw, Poland,” said the statement. It will be recalled that the Federal Government engaged Air Peace and other airlines to evacuate over 2,000 Nigerian nationals from neighbouring countries such as Poland, Romania, Hungary and Slovakia. (NAN). 